      <description>&lt;script src=&#34;https://ssp3nc3r.github.io/post/tables-in-tooltips/index_files/header-attrs/header-attrs.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;link href=&#34;https://ssp3nc3r.github.io/post/tables-in-tooltips/index_files/tabwid/tabwid.css&#34; rel=&#34;stylesheet&#34; /&gt;&#xA;&lt;script src=&#34;https://ssp3nc3r.github.io/post/tables-in-tooltips/index_files/htmlwidgets/htmlwidgets.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;script src=&#34;https://ssp3nc3r.github.io/post/tables-in-tooltips/index_files/d3-bundle/d3-bundle.min.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;script src=&#34;https://ssp3nc3r.github.io/post/tables-in-tooltips/index_files/d3-lasso/d3-lasso.min.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;script src=&#34;https://ssp3nc3r.github.io/post/tables-in-tooltips/index_files/save-svg-as-png/save-svg-as-png.min.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;link href=&#34;https://ssp3nc3r.github.io/post/tables-in-tooltips/index_files/ggiraphjs/ggiraphjs.min.css&#34; rel=&#34;stylesheet&#34; /&gt;&#xA;&lt;script src=&#34;https://ssp3nc3r.github.io/post/tables-in-tooltips/index_files/ggiraphjs/ggiraphjs.min.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;script src=&#34;https://ssp3nc3r.github.io/post/tables-in-tooltips/index_files/girafe-binding/girafe.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;With interactive communications, we frequently encourage the graphic to provide some form of &lt;em&gt;overview&lt;/em&gt;, and use interactions for adding &lt;em&gt;details on demand&lt;/em&gt;. For these details, tables provide a flexible way to organize the information. And we can link the view of such tables to user actions like a &lt;em&gt;pointer hover event&lt;/em&gt; where the table of details is in a &lt;em&gt;tooltip&lt;/em&gt;. In this tutorial, we construct an &lt;code&gt;html&lt;/code&gt; table for our tooltip so that we can organize lots of details on demand.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
